================================================================================
3. Studied, but not vendored
================================================================================

Clojure itself (https://github.com/clojure/clojure, EPL-1.0) is the
semantic specification cljgo targets: its behavior is the oracle the
conformance suite is verified against, and its Java source is the
reference the reader, analyzer and data structures were built from. No
Clojure source is vendored here.

cljs2go (https://github.com/hraberg/cljs2go) and let-go
(https://github.com/nooga/let-go) were read as reference while designing
the emitter and the concurrency model. No code from either is present in
this repository.
